The facility would store the waste from the Kriko nuclear power plant.
The Bosnians, holding banners with the words "I want a healthy future" and "Stop – (river) Una needs us", said that the radioactive waste dump could threaten the Una River and the lives of about 250,000 residents.
We have to say no,
told the crowd Miroslav Drljaca, mayor of Novi Grad municipality.
