The Act on the State Commission on Pedophilia came into force
The provisions of the law have been in force since Thursday.
According to them, the tasks of the commission will include, among others, issuing provisions on the registration of perpetrators of sexual offences, notifying the relevant authorities about the suspicion of committing the crime of paedophilia, but also about cases of not notifying the competent authority about the suspicion of the crime of paedophilia.
The Commission will also identify negligence and omissions in clarifying cases of sexual abuse.
It is about neglect and omissions of state bodies, non-governmental organizations, entities and institutions conducting educational, educational, caring, cultural and related to physical culture, rest and treatment, as well as professional self-governments, churches and religious unions, including ecclesiastical legal persons and individuals.
The task of the committee will also be to conduct preventive and educational activities.
The Commission is to be a body independent of other state authorities.
It is to consist of seven members: three – appointed by the Sejm by a three-fifths majority in the presence of at least half of the statutory number of deputies; one – appointed by the Senate by a three-fifths majority in the presence of at least half of the statutory number of senators, as well as one member appointed by the president, prime minister and child rights advocate.
Members of the committee will have to have a higher legal, medical or psychological education, among other things, and "enjoy an unblemished opinion".
Members, senators, members of the European Parliament, and those in charge of the state can not sit on the committee.
Among the entities that will be able to submit candidates for committee members were: the Supreme Bar Council, the National Council of Legal Advisers, the National Council of the Judiciary, the National Council of Prosecutors, the Supreme Chamber of Physicians, the National Chamber of Psychologists and non-governmental organizations whose statutory tasks for at least two years included activities related to children's rights, in particular those related to protection and counteracting violence, including sexual violence.
Candidates for committee members appointed by the Sejm may also be nominated by the Marshal of the Sejm or at least 35 deputies.
In turn, candidates for a member of the Commission appointed by the Senate may also be nominated by the Speaker of the Senate or at least 7 senators.
The chairman of the committee will be elected – from among the members of the committee – by the Sejm by a simple majority.
The term of the committee will last for seven years.
A representative of the ombudsman will be able to take part in the work of the committee, with an advisory vote and at the invitation of the President.
Under the law, "anyone may report to the Commission the suspicion of sexual abuse or the suspicion of not notifying the competent authority of the suspicion of sexual abuse."
The application may be submitted in writing, orally to the minutes or by electronic means of communication.
Such a report is to be promptly forwarded to the prosecutor's office competent for the victim's place of residence.
In the event of judicial proceedings, the committee has the right to inspect the court files and obtain information about the proceedings.
The Commission may also participate in proceedings conducted on the rights of the auxiliary prosecutor (with the consent of the injured person or his legal guardian).
The first report of the commission is to be prepared and made available within one year from the date of entry into force of the Act.
U.S. Congress Agrees to Sell 32 F-35 Aircraft to Poland
The U.S. Congress for 15 days after the State Department approved the possible purchase of 32 F-35 multi-purpose fighter jets by Poland did not object to this transaction, which means that the last condition was met before the purchase negotiations began.
The decision of Congress, although not unexpected, is of great political importance.
"After approval of the sale by the State Department, and now by Congress, I don't see any major obstacles," said John V. Venable, senior defense policy counsel for the Washington, D.C. conservative think tank Heritage Foundation.
The expert explained that under the Arms Export Control Act 1976, the federal government, represented by the State Department, must notify Congress of any planned sale of arms abroad 15 days before the signing of the agreement if the value of such a transaction, in the case of arms sales to a NATO member country, exceeds $50 million.
The proposed purchase of 32 F-35 fighter jets by Poland is estimated at $6.5 billion. This amount includes costs of technical and logistical assistance, auxiliary equipment and pilot training.
The main supplier of F-35 aircraft – if this transaction is finally finalized – will be the American arms company Lockheed Martin, and its subcontractor is the engine manufacturer for the F-35A fighter jets Pratt and Whitney.
Proposals for the purchase of American fifth generation F-35 fighters on behalf of the Polish authorities were made in May by the Minister of Defence Mariusz Błaszczak.
The Polish offer was discussed in June this year during a meeting between President Andrzej Duda and President Donald Trump in the White House.
The implementation of this agreement, if finalized, will be overseen by Pentagon representatives under the Foreign Military Sales Program (FMS).
As part of the FMS program, Poland has already acquired, among others, the Patriot anti-missile system.
The price of one F-35 fighter at the time of Poland's bid for the purchase was – without armament and technical assistance – about $89.2 million.
According to the PAP, U.S. military experts who wanted to remain anonymous, such a price given in the preliminary negotiations was "a maximum price, much higher than the price to be negotiated."
"Prices are plummeting, currently the price of one F-35 is under $80 million, much less than the cost of a Eurofighter, which has no such advantages as an F-35," Venable pointed out.
The PAP spokespeople expressed hope that the final negotiations of the transaction on the purchase of American combat aircraft by Poland will end later this year.
The possible participation of Polish subcontractors in this transaction – i.e. offset – will be discussed directly with American manufacturers of F-35 fighter jets.
What is the replacement band for the show "Payton Hobart's Choices" on Netflix?
Caregivers and parents with the disorder above pretend that their healthy child is eating sick.
