The well-known Sydney Bay is one of the most polluted waterways in the country, which is affected annually by a volume of pollution equal to the capacity of about 15 Olympic pools.
These frightening statistics make one of our biggest tourist assets at the same time one of our dirtiest reservoirs.
According to a new footage entitled "Sydney Bay – Up and Down", the waters in the area of Australia's most popular city are full of buttresses, plastic nets and bottles, lost shoes and pieces of clothing, and even dead animals, all flowing into the bay along with rainwater.
