Tasmanian devils can provide clues on how to treat cancer
Tasmanian devils may hold the key to cancer treatment – researchers have made a breakthrough discovery that could revolutionize patient therapy
Researchers in the field of medicine have discovered a way to mask certain cancer cells
The researchers found that the same process occurs in Tasmanian devils and humans.
There is hope that this discovery will bring new treatments for cancer patients.
What do Tasmanian devils and humans have in common?
